23:["$","section",null,{"style":{"background":"#f9f9f9","padding":"60px 20px"},"children":["$","div",null,{"style":{"maxWidth":"900px","margin":"0 auto"},"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"32px","marginBottom":"30px","textAlign":"center"},"children":"Patio Design FAQs"}],[["$","div","0",{"style":{"marginBottom":"20px","background":"#fff","padding":"25px","borderRadius":"8px","boxShadow":"0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"20px","marginBottom":"10px","color":"#B58E3B"},"children":"Do I need a permit for a patio in Northern Virginia?"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"lineHeight":"1.6","color":"#444"},"children":"Most ground-level patios that do not alter the major grading or drainage of the property do not require a building permit. However, if your patio includes retaining walls over 2 feet, electrical lines for kitchens, or sits in a designated RPA (Resource Protection Area), county permits are required. Loudoun Decks handles all of this compliance for you."}]]}],["$","div","1",{"style":{"marginBottom":"20px","background":"#fff","padding":"25px","borderRadius":"8px","boxShadow":"0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"20px","marginBottom":"10px","color":"#B58E3B"},"children":"How much does a custom patio cost?"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"lineHeight":"1.6","color":"#444"},"children":"Custom patio projects in Northern Virginia typically start at $15,000+ for natural stone and premium pavers. Pricing varies based on square footage, material selection, grading requirements, and integrated features like fire pits or outdoor kitchens."}]]}],["$","div","2",{"style":{"marginBottom":"20px","background":"#fff","padding":"25px","borderRadius":"8px","boxShadow":"0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"20px","marginBottom":"10px","color":"#B58E3B"},"children":"How much does a bluestone patio cost compared to stamped concrete?"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"lineHeight":"1.6","color":"#444"},"children":"Bluestone is a premium natural material, so the upfront material and labor costs are higher than poured or stamped concrete. However, stamped concrete is highly prone to cracking during Virginia's freeze-thaw cycles. Bluestone, laid on a flexible aggregate base, rarely cracks and can be easily repaired stone-by-stone, offering a vastly superior long-term ROI."}]]}],["$","div","3",{"style":{"marginBottom":"20px","background":"#fff","padding":"25px","borderRadius":"8px","boxShadow":"0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"20px","marginBottom":"10px","color":"#B58E3B"},"children":"How do you handle water runoff and drainage?"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"lineHeight":"1.6","color":"#444"},"children":"Proper drainage is the hallmark of professional hardscaping. We grade all our patios with a subtle, imperceptible slope (typically 1/8 inch per foot) directing water away from your home's foundation. If your yard has existing water pooling issues, we integrate French drains and catch basins beneath the patio structure."}]]}],["$","div","4",{"style":{"marginBottom":"20px","background":"#fff","padding":"25px","borderRadius":"8px","boxShadow":"0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"20px","marginBottom":"10px","color":"#B58E3B"},"children":"Can I put a hot tub on my patio?"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"lineHeight":"1.6","color":"#444"},"children":"Absolutely. If you plan to install a hot tub, we simply adjust the depth and compaction of our crushed stone aggregate base in that specific footprint to support the immense weight (often exceeding 4,000 lbs filled) without shifting the surrounding stones."}]]}]]]}]}]
